Privacy Policy

Last Updated: [Enter Date]

This Privacy Policy explains how Quran Video Uploader (“the App”) collects, uses, and protects your information.

We respect your privacy and handle all Islamic and personal content with care.

1. Information We Collect
a. TikTok Authentication

If you log in with TikTok:

We may receive your TikTok username and basic profile info.

We do NOT receive or store your password.

b. Usage Data

We may collect:

App usage logs

Error logs

Uploaded video metadata (file name, upload status only)

c. No Sensitive Data Stored

We do not store:

Personal IDs

Religious opinions

Location data

TikTok passwords

Quran audio content itself

2. How We Use Your Information

We use the information to:

Authenticate your account with TikTok

Upload videos on your behalf

Improve the App’s performance

Fix errors and bugs

3. How We Store and Protect Data

Limited personal data may be stored securely.

Data is encrypted where possible.

We do not sell or share your data with third parties.

4. Sharing of Data

We may share data only when necessary:

With TikTok APIs to upload videos

With legal authorities if required by law

We never share your data for advertising or marketing.

5. Your Rights

Depending on your region, you may:

Request deletion of your data

Request a copy of your stored data

Stop using the App at any time

You may contact us to manage your data.

6. Children’s Privacy

The App is not intended for children under 13.
If you are under 13, do not use the App.

7. Changes to Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy as needed.
Updates will be posted with a new date.

8. Contact

For privacy concerns:
Email: [your email]
